â“ Checkpoint Questions

Q1: What does AF_INET mean in socket()?
A1: It specifies IPv4.

Q2: Why do we use htons(PORT)?
A2: To convert the port number to network byte order.

Q3: What does listen(server_fd, 3) do?
A3: It puts the server in a listening state, with a queue for up to 3 pending connections.
